\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 1. Overview\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 Nuclear Fallout ML Simulator is a Unity asset for Monte Carlo nuclear fallout simulation with ML clustering, probability mapping, and optional Cesium 3D globe visualization.\par
\pard\sb60\sa60\b Pipeline:\b0  Physics (Gaussian Plume/Puff) \u8594? Monte Carlo (N scenarios) \u8594? ML Clustering (K-Means / ClusteringGrid) \u8594? Probability Map \u8594? Export (GeoJSON / CZML / CSV)\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 All computation is handled by CSharpNumerics. This Unity asset provides visualization, UI, and export integration.\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 2. Requirements\b0\fs24\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  Unity 2021.3 or newer\par
\bullet  CSharpNumerics.dll (included in Assets/Plugins/CSharpNumerics/)\par
\bullet  Optional: Cesium for Unity (com.cesium.unity) for 3D globe visualization\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 3. Installation\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb60\sa60\b Step 1:\b0  Import the package into your Unity project via the Asset Store or by importing the .unitypackage file.\par
\pard\sb60\sa60\b Step 2:\b0  Verify that \f1 Assets/Plugins/CSharpNumerics/CSharpNumerics.dll\f0  is present. If not, build it from the included source or download from NuGet.\par
\pard\sb60\sa60\b Step 3:\b0  Open the demo scene at \f1 NuclearFalloutML/Demo/Scenes/FalloutDemo.unity\f0  and enter Play Mode to verify installation.\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 4. Quick Start (Step-by-Step Tutorial)\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Method A: Using the Demo Scene (Recommended)\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 1. Open \f1 NuclearFalloutML/Demo/Scenes/FalloutDemo.unity\f0\par
2. Select the "Fallout Simulation" GameObject in the Hierarchy\par
3. In the Inspector, adjust parameters under Simulation Config (source coordinates, wind, MC iterations, etc.)\par
4. Press Play \u8212? the simulation runs automatically and displays a probability heatmap\par
5. Use the interactive controls (see Section 6) to explore results\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Method B: Adding to Your Own Scene\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 1. Create an empty GameObject in your scene\par
2. Add the \f1 DemoSimulation\f0  component (Add Component \u8594? NuclearFalloutML.Demo \u8594? DemoSimulation)\par
3. Configure parameters in the Inspector\par
4. Enter Play Mode \u8212? the demo auto-creates its own Camera, Canvas, and heatmap visualization\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Method C: Production Setup with Manager\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 1. Add a \f1 FalloutSimulationManager\f0  component to a GameObject\par
2. Add a \f1 CesiumFalloutRenderer\f0  component (requires Cesium for Unity installed)\par
3. Configure parameters via the custom Inspector\par
4. Enter Play Mode and click "Run Simulation"\par
5. Results are visualized on the Cesium globe and exported to the configured directory\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 5. Demo Scene Guide\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 The included demo scene (\f1 FalloutDemo.unity\f0 ) contains:\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b Main Camera\b0  \u8212? Standard camera (the demo may reposition it at runtime)\par
\bullet  \b Directional Light\b0  \u8212? Scene lighting for visual quality\par
\bullet  \b Fallout Simulation\b0  \u8212? GameObject with the DemoSimulation component pre-configured\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 When you press Play, the DemoSimulation component:\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 1. Builds a CSharpNumerics RiskScenario pipeline\par
2. Runs Monte Carlo simulation with N scenarios\par
3. Performs ML clustering analysis (K-Means with multiple K values)\par
4. Creates a full-screen Canvas with a probability heatmap overlay on an OpenStreetMap background\par
5. Displays a color legend and real-time statistics\par
6. Exports results to GeoJSON, CZML, and CSV in the configured export directory\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 No manual setup is required. The demo is fully self-contained.\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 6. Interactive Controls\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 While the demo is running in Play Mode:\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b Left/Right Arrow\b0  \u8212? Step through time indices (view different time snapshots)\par
\bullet  \b Space\b0  \u8212? Play/pause automatic time advancement (0.5 seconds per step)\par
\bullet  \b C\b0  \u8212? Cycle view mode: Probability \u8594? Concentration \u8594? Activity \u8594? Dose \u8594? Clusters\par
\bullet  \b M\b0  \u8212? Toggle ML statistics panel (shows clustering pipeline rankings)\par
\bullet  \b Up/Down Arrow\b0  \u8212? Adjust heatmap overlay opacity\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 7. Configuration Parameters\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb60\sa60 All parameters are exposed in the Unity Inspector via the SimulationConfig class.\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Source Location (WGS84)\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b SourceLatitude\b0  (double, -90 to 90, default: 55.605) \u8212? Event latitude\par
\bullet  \b SourceLongitude\b0  (double, -180 to 180, default: 13.004) \u8212? Event longitude\par
\bullet  \b SourceAltitudeMeters\b0  (double, default: 50) \u8212? Source altitude in meters\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Source Term\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b EmissionRateKgPerS\b0  (double, default: 5.0) \u8212? Mass emission rate in kg/s\par
\bullet  \b StackHeightMeters\b0  (float, 0-2000, default: 50) \u8212? Effective release height in meters\par
\bullet  \b Radioisotope\b0  (string, default: "Cs137") \u8212? Material type (Cs137, I131, Sr90)\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Atmospheric Conditions\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b WindSpeedMs\b0  (float, 0.5-50, default: 10) \u8212? Mean wind speed in m/s\par
\bullet  \b WindDirectionX\b0  (float, default: 1) \u8212? Wind direction X component (east)\par
\bullet  \b WindDirectionY\b0  (float, default: 0) \u8212? Wind direction Y component (north)\par
\bullet  \b Stability\b0  (enum, default: D_Neutral) \u8212? Pasquill-Gifford stability class (A-F)\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Monte Carlo Settings\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b MonteCarloIterations\b0  (int, 10-100000, default: 20) \u8212? Number of scenarios to simulate\par
\bullet  \b RandomSeed\b0  (int, default: 42) \u8212? Seed for reproducibility (0 = random)\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Scenario Variation\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b WindSpeedVariationMin/Max\b0  (float) \u8212? Wind speed variation range for MC\par
\bullet  \b WindDirectionJitterDeg\b0  (float, 0-90, default: 15) \u8212? Direction jitter sigma in degrees\par
\bullet  \b EmissionRateVariationMin/Max\b0  (double) \u8212? Emission rate variation range\par
\bullet  \b StabilityWeightC/D/E\b0  (float, 0-1) \u8212? Stability class probability weights (should sum to ~1)\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Grid Settings\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b GridExtentMeters\b0  (float, default: 500) \u8212? Half-extent from source in meters\par
\bullet  \b GridAltitudeMaxMeters\b0  (float, default: 100) \u8212? Maximum altitude in meters\par
\bullet  \b GridStepMeters\b0  (float, 1-100, default: 50) \u8212? Grid cell size in meters\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Time Settings\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b TimeStartSeconds\b0  (double, default: 0) \u8212? Simulation start time\par
\bullet  \b TimeEndSeconds\b0  (double, default: 600) \u8212? Simulation end time\par
\bullet  \b TimeStepSeconds\b0  (double, default: 60) \u8212? Time step duration\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Plume Mode\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b PlumeMode\b0  (enum: SteadyState / Transient, default: Transient)\par
\bullet  \b PuffReleaseSeconds\b0  (double, default: 10) \u8212? Puff release duration (Transient mode only)\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Export\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30\bullet  \b ExportDirectory\b0  (string, default: "FalloutExport") \u8212? Output directory relative to project root\par
\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 8. Script Reference\b0\fs24\par
