\pard\keepn\sb360\sa120\b\fs32 12. Troubleshooting\b0\fs24\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Problem: "CSharpNumerics not found" compiler error\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 Solution: Verify that CSharpNumerics.dll exists at Assets/Plugins/CSharpNumerics/CSharpNumerics.dll. If missing, rebuild from source or download from NuGet.\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Problem: Demo shows black screen\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 Solution: Check the Console for error messages. The simulation runs asynchronously and may take a few seconds to complete. Ensure MonteCarloIterations is not set too high (start with 20 for testing).\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Problem: Cesium visualization not working\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 Solution: Cesium for Unity (com.cesium.unity) must be installed separately. The CesiumFalloutRenderer requires #CESIUM_AVAILABLE define which is automatically set via versionDefines when Cesium is detected.\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Problem: Export files not created\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 Solution: Check the ExportDirectory field in SimulationConfig. The directory is relative to the project root. Ensure the simulation completed successfully before exporting.\par
\pard\sb120\sa60\b Problem: Heatmap appears empty or all green\b0\par
\pard\li360\sb30\sa30 Solution: Increase the GridExtentMeters to cover a larger area, or increase EmissionRateKgPerS. The ProbabilityThreshold (default: 1e-6) filters out very low values.\par
